# Memory

[adminuser@fedora ~]$ free -h
               total        used        free      shared  buff/cache   available
Mem:           1.9Gi       1.3Gi       213Mi        12Mi       405Mi       521Mi
Swap:          1.9Gi       422Mi       1.5Gi
      
The columns in the output represent:

total: Total amount of memory.
used: Memory currently in use.
free: Memory that is not being used.
shared: Memory shared with other systems.
buff/cache: Memory used for buffers and cache.
available: Estimate of memory available for new applications without swapping.
This command provides a clear and easily understandable view of the systemâ€™s memory usage.

